Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.59,0:00:04.30,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two people's deductions and suspense\Nfill the gulf between love and hate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.30,0:00:05.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We've almost figured out\Nthe truth about the bomb case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:07.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Metro Police\Ndetectives' love story!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.98,0:00:09.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth\Nfor what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.68,0:00:11.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.68,0:00:13.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name?\NDetective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.05,0:01:48.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At a victory parade for the Tokyo Spirits,\Nwe, the Detective Boys,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.81,0:01:51.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}ran into Detective Sato and her\Nfellow officers, who were in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:55.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They were conducting an investigation\Nbecause a fax had arrived at HQ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.93,0:02:00.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}warning that something was going\Nto happen during the parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.30,0:02:03.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then,\NDetective Takagi's car...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.30,0:02:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.93,0:02:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.97,0:02:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Shiratori!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.67,0:02:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Where's Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.95,0:02:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One does not ordinarily survive\Ngetting caught in such an explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.69,0:02:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Detective Takagi is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.37,0:02:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.95,0:02:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did say "ordinarily".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.40,0:02:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What's that\Nsupposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.70,0:02:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got away by the\Nskin of my teeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.39,0:02:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so don't talk like\NI didn't make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.13,0:02:42.16,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While we were trying to figure out\Nif the bomber appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:46.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}on the video that Mitsuhiko\Nwas recording near the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.92,0:02:49.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!\NAnother bomb went off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.67,0:02:51.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.07,0:02:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one was at a phone booth\Nin front of the park in Haido City.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.62,0:02:57.89,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Judging by the type of bomb,\Nit's probably the same person behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.89,0:03:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the suspect is\Nnot targeting the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.45,0:03:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just someone who took his hatred\Nof the Tokyo Spirits way too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:10.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is it really just about\Nhating the Spirits?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.67,0:03:13.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:16.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This videotape\Nthat Mitsuhiko took...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.33,0:03:22.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is there something on it\Nthat will identify the bomber?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:25.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:28.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just what will it show?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Over there, over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ain't that chick\Nsuspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.93,0:03:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's just been\Nglaring at the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.71,0:03:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she's got this really\Nannoyed look on her face!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.13,0:03:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because she's mad that Mitsuhiko's\Ncamera is pointing up at her miniskirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, well, that wasn't\Nmy intention...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.23,0:04:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about this dude\Nwith the mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.78,0:04:04.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been looking around\Nwith his head down, hasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.25,0:04:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a good look\Nat his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.55,0:04:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's holding a child's shoe,\Nisn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably came with his wife,\Nwho was holding their child,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.59,0:04:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and both of the child's shoes\Nhappened to fall off,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.93,0:04:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he was looking for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.43,0:04:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.39,0:04:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you notice anything,\NDetective Takagi, speak up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:32.15,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And after this,\Nwe need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.15,0:04:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.70,0:04:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you even watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.51,0:04:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've watched it three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.89,0:04:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But it's the same\Nevery time I watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.67,0:04:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think someone in the crowd is suspicious,\Neveryone will look suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and if you don't think anyone is suspicious,\Nnobody will look suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.25,0:04:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trying to pick the bomber\Nout of this is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:04:57.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He {\i1}is{\i0} right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.59,0:05:00.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No doubt the bomber\Nthought the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:04.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the bomber made sure to take the tape\Nout of the camera when stealing it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.71,0:05:07.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the bomber {\i1}thought{\i0}\Nhe had been filmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.75,0:05:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though nothing\Nwas actually filmed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.23,0:05:16.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nothing filmed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.07,0:05:20.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait, if nothing\Nwas filmed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.95,0:05:22.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:27.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Aha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.55,0:05:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Say, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.99,0:05:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.70,0:05:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's no good,\Nisn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.36,0:05:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.49,0:05:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The bomber might not have done it\Nbecause something was on the tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.62,0:05:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but to destroy the evidence that\Nthere was nothing on the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean\Nby that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.52,0:05:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, there's one thing\NI need to confirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.73,0:06:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Conan!\NWhat do you mean by that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About nothing on tape\Nbeing suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.62,0:06:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there wasn't anything\Non the tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.14,0:06:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't there be no need\Nfor the bomber to steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.01,0:06:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait up! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.46,0:06:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.87,0:06:19.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.05,0:06:20.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's exactly\Nas I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.66,0:06:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Is there something\Nwrong with the mail drop?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what time it was that Mitsuhiko\Nclimbed onto the mail drop, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.06,0:06:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't remember\Nnothing like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can find that out\Nfrom the videotape, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.18,0:06:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the timestamp\Nrecorded onto the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.15,0:06:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.03,0:06:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.93,0:06:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Starting from when I zoomed in\Non Hide in the distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.86,0:06:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.21,0:06:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2:23 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after that, we ran\Ninto Detective Sato.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.86,0:07:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until Mitsuhiko stopped\Ntaping, at 2:38 PM,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.69,0:07:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we stayed right here\Nnext to this mail drop, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.30,0:07:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What's important\Nabout that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, take a look\Nat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pickup timetable\Nposted on this mail drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.62,0:07:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under "Holidays" it says\N"Approximately 14:30."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means it says\Naround 2:30 PM, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.07,0:07:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means we didn't see something\Nwe should have seen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aha! The mailman's car!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.03,0:07:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nhe never came by to pick up the mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.58,0:07:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he couldn't come because\Nthe parade was blocking the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the parade route was chosen\Nso as not to interfere with official business.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.62,0:07:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Currently traffic is one-way\Nbecause of the parade,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he should still\Nhave been able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.77,0:07:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.09,0:08:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't the road being blocked\Nmake him at least 8 minutes late?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.11,0:08:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if there weren't any\Nparticular traffic bottlenecks,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the posted mail pickup times\Nare in increments of 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there were a discrepancy\Nof more than 5 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they would think that something\Nmust have happened, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was the bomber who stole\NMitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s tape, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would postal vehicles\Nhave to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.72,0:08:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why go to the effort\Nof stealing the tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.72,0:08:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were left alone,\Nnobody would have noticed anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.37,0:08:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now, it's like coming out and saying\Nthat there's something on the tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.73,0:08:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I don't think\Nthey intended to take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.13,0:08:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were just us kids\Nhere to see the parade...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.74,0:08:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.85,0:08:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mini-patrol car!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They saw you chatting with her\Nin front of the mail drop,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so they tried to\Ndestroy the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.75,0:09:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a bombing\Nhappened right there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the bomber could possibly\Nhave been caught on tape,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.38,0:09:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and naturally, the police\Nwould check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.03,0:09:16.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since we know\Nthe police,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.94,0:09:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would be an especially short time\Nbefore the video was checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.49,0:09:23.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what they\Nwere afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.44,0:09:28.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably noticed\NMitsuhiko's camera
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:34.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,only after planting the bomb near\Nthe drop box, under Detective Takagi's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:38.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They couldn't grab the bomb\Nfrom under the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so they had to steal\Nthe tape instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.53,0:09:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't the bomber send a fax\Nto the police hinting at their crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:54.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they went to the effort of getting the police together and blowing up the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.90,0:09:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they know the police\Nwould search desperately for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:02.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they meant\Nto distract the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.67,0:10:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by making it look like the same\Nbomber from three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.59,0:10:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I don't know what\Nkind of case that may have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.99,0:10:14.56,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just like the case\Nfrom three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.56,0:10:19.42,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}there is a good chance that the bomber\Nintends to kill police officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.57,0:10:23.94,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You just looked\Nlike {\i1}him{\i0} then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.26,0:10:29.05,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems that the one Sato{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10}\Nwas really trying to save was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:33.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And after this,\Nwe need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That leaves the question\Nof the bomber's objective...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.09,0:10:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, their target\Nwasn't the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.97,0:10:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and it had nothing to do\Nwith a grudge against the Spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.19,0:10:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my deductions\Nare correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.80,0:10:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,their target is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.07,0:10:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't have\Nproof yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.03,0:10:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'd like you and Detective Takagi\Nto check on something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:10:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave it to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.45,0:11:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi,\Nare you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.54,0:11:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.55,0:11:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'm listening,\NI'm listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.63,0:11:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.11,0:11:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\NI found a mail drop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, what's the location\Nand collection time for that mail drop?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.14,0:11:22.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Under the foot bridge,\Ntwo lights past the other mail drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.27,0:11:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The collection time is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.38,0:11:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says about 14:35.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.42,0:11:28.27,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.27,0:11:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... Mitsuhiko here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found one in front of the\Nconvenience store on Block 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.77,0:11:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The collection time is\Nabout 14:45.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.24,0:11:39.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Captain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.31,0:11:42.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found one.\NNext to the park on Block 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.56,0:11:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time is 14:55.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.31,0:11:48.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Genta.\NWhy are you talking so quietly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.17,0:11:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.06,0:11:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I took a shortcut\Nthrough someone's yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.80,0:11:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thought I was a thief\Nand chased me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.40,0:11:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so now I'm hiding from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.81,0:12:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just leaves Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.36,0:12:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.89,0:12:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woman in Black here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.31,0:12:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The location of the mail drop\Nis about 150 meters left
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.18,0:12:17.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of the Block 3 post office,\Nnext to the bus stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.99,0:12:20.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The collection time is 16:25.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can see you guys\Nfrom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.10,0:12:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:25.36,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.70,0:12:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, the pickup time at the mail drop\Nright in front of the post office is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.53,0:12:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,16:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.18,0:12:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if I check everyone's info\Nagainst the map,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.84,0:12:44.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it looks like this\Nis the mail pickup route.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.52,0:12:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks to be exactly\Nas you said, Shin'ichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.64,0:12:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to be going further and\Nfurther away from the parade route.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's a Sunday\Nright before bills come due.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.68,0:12:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we just have to wait\Nfor Detective Takagi to contact us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there aren't any accidents\Nor roadwork in this area today,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.25,0:13:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the reason the mail van didn't come\Nto get the mail is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.99,0:13:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter,\NTsutsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're dropping off the mail\Nyou picked up, go around back and—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.95,0:13:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.91,0:13:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a whole bunch of\Nweird stuff mixed in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.52,0:13:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'd like everyone to\Ntake a look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.44,0:13:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so could you open\Nthe front door?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.15,0:14:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it. I'll do that\Nright now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.45,0:14:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Thank you.\NSorry for the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.70,0:14:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no trouble\Nat all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.36,0:14:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is all this weird mail\Nyou were telling me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.37,0:14:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!\NWhat are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.68,0:14:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad, my bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.37,0:14:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I want to show is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.16,0:14:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This, Mr. Postal Worker...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A handgun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.97,0:14:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You in the back, stick 'em up\Nand come up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.08,0:14:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mess around\Nor you're dead meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.15,0:14:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, get a move on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:14:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too!\NGet the lead out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.33,0:15:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quit dawdling!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, now\Nhand over all the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.44,0:15:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the day before bills come due,\Nso I bet you're loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.20,0:15:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you picked the same day\Nas the Tokyo Spirits victory parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.86,0:15:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A day when there wouldn't be\Nas many workers at the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.46,0:15:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you used the fax and bombs to pretend\Nto be the bomber from three years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.79,0:15:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to lure away the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.16,0:15:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made it look like an attack on the Spirits\Nto throw the police off the trail,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.71,0:15:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so they would follow\Nthe parade route,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while you attacked the post office\Nwith your stolen mail van.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.69,0:15:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it wasn't a very well\Nthought-out plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.68,0:15:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you\Nyapping on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.56,0:15:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and\Nget up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.39,0:15:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard him.\NEveryone, hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.08,0:15:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speed it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.71,0:16:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, how are there so many\Npeople here on a Sunday?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may all be civil servants, but unlike\Nthe post office, which has holidays,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we're open 24/7,\N365 days a year...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.52,0:16:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police department!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.28,0:16:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the fuzz!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.43,0:16:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've released the postal workers\Nwho were tied up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.06,0:16:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.41,0:16:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.37,0:16:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.35,0:16:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't try\Nanything funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.39,0:16:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Damn it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.39,0:16:54.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And so, the post office\Nrobbers were arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.06,0:17:04.84,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and with the rest of the group, who had\Nbeen out elsewhere placing the bombs,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.84,0:17:07.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}were also caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.89,0:17:11.08,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And that evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm surprised\Nyou were able to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.37,0:17:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the bombers were actually\Nplanning a post-office robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.28,0:17:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, the kids\Ngave us the hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.24,0:17:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r},\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.83,0:17:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's definitely\Nno ordinary kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.44,0:17:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.63,0:17:33.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nsorry about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About slapping you\Nout of the blue like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.13,0:17:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It hurt, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.44,0:17:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.83,0:17:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}was{\i0} my fault\Nfor ignoring orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you, Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?\NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.73,0:17:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You burned your hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.\NWell, it does still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.66,0:18:10.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It still stings a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.86,0:18:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but a little spit\Nand it'll be all better!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I see...\NW-Well, that's good to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.85,0:18:26.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.57,0:18:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you want\Nto talk to me about earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.86,0:18:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.91,0:18:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.49,0:18:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's call off our date.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.25,0:18:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm cursed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.30,0:18:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Cursed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.75,0:18:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I always wind up losing\Neveryone who's important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.81,0:18:59.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.81,0:19:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grade-school\Ngym teacher...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.48,0:19:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My {\rHonorifics - Dialogue}senpai{\r} from\Nbaseball club...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.10,0:19:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.94,0:19:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And {\i1}him{\i0} too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go through\Nanything that painful ever again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.91,0:19:21.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sato{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.63,0:19:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So for now, let's just remain\Nfellow police officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.29,0:19:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:45.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!\NGo for it, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Push! Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.52,0:19:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Push, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.41,0:19:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys\Nare a bit heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.73,0:20:05.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sato{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.36,0:20:07.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Takagi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-kun{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:13.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll never...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.09,0:20:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.87,0:20:28.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right... We were never\Na good match to begin with...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.48,0:20:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! You'll find someone so much cuter,\Nsomeone who's a better fit for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.78,0:20:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.21,0:20:37.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.03,0:20:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.82,0:20:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, catch you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.88,0:20:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.91,0:20:56.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sato{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.54,0:22:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong,\NDetective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.81,0:22:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your face looks pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:23:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ain't you been eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.67,0:23:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're here for questioning\Non the post office burglary case!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.50,0:23:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you haven't\Ngotten over getting dumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.21,0:23:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.81,0:23:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-H-How'd you know\Nabout that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.76,0:23:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yo, Takagi!\NHow's it hangin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You look tired!\NWant me to handle the questioning?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.66,0:23:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.79,0:23:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Takagi, let me\Nmassage your shoulders!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.06,0:23:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about some\Ncoffee, Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.24,0:23:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.71,0:23:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're hungry,\NI've got some rice crackers...{Sembei}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.08,0:23:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Eat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.37,0:23:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! Detective Takagi\Nsure is popular!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.11,0:23:44.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, I don't think\Nthat's what it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.37,0:23:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when we arrived, she had such\Na shocked and scared look on her face!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.81,0:23:56.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't look like she was\Npretending at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:24:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if what\Nhe just said is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.33,0:24:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is kind of hard\Nto believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.34,0:24:05.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.68,0:24:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!\NThe culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.35,0:24:17.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.40,0:24:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Recycling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.41,0:24:23.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The next episode is the last broadcast of the year!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.87,0:24:24.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,For us...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.57,0:24:25.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,In a 2-hour New Year's special...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.96,0:24:27.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's our time to shine!
